🔗 Needs External Integration — Fix Later
KYC (requires govt API or third-party vendor)
Liveness detection — needs DigiLocker, UIDAI Aadhaar e-KYC, or a paid SDK (HyperVerge, IDnow, Jumio, Onfido) — all require business agreements
PAN/Aadhaar verification against government DB — NSDL and UIDAI APIs require RBI-registered entity status
RBI KYC compliance — requires NBFC license or a regulated banking partner; can't be coded around
AI Transaction Risk (requires real data)
ML fraud model — needs a labelled dataset of real fraudulent vs legitimate transactions; minimum 50k–100k labelled examples before a model is useful
Credit bureau integration — CIBIL / Experian India APIs require a formal credit institution agreement
Device fingerprinting — needs a third-party SDK (Fingerprint.js Pro, ThreatMetrix, Sardine) with a paid plan
Behavioural biometrics — typing cadence, swipe patterns — requires a dedicated SDK and months of baseline collection
RAG Knowledge Base (requires corpus work)
Finance-domain embedding model — a general embedding model doesn't understand "NACH mandate", "IMPS float", "NPA provisioning"; fine-tuning requires a curated finance corpus (~10k+ documents)
Anthropic Retrieval / managed RAG — moving from self-hosted Chroma/pgvector to a managed retrieval service requires an enterprise Anthropic agreement
RBI circulars auto-ingestion pipeline — RBI publishes ~200 circulars/year; building an auto-scrape-and-ingest pipeline is engineering work but no external dependency
Triage Agent (requires live system access)
Live Grafana metrics in agent context — agent needs Grafana HTTP API key + tool-calling wired to fetch real dashboard data
Runbook execution — agent calling Kubernetes (kubectl rollout restart), PagerDuty alert creation, or Slack escalation requires tool-calling infrastructure and IAM permissions
Real incident history ingestion — needs actual production incidents to build a meaningful KB; synthetic ones produce hallucinated root causes


